                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "iXCCr",
                      "fill": "$--foreground-primary",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Sure! These are two strategies for handling hash collisions:\n\nChaining — each bucket holds a linked list. When two keys hash to the same index, the new entry is appended to that list.\n\nOpen addressing — when a collision occurs, the algorithm probes for the next empty slot in the array.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.5,
                      "fontFamily": "$--font-body",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
